DEFINITIONS AND INTERPRETATION

In this Agreement:

“Affiliate” means, in relation to a party, a subsidiary or holding company of that party or any other subsidiary of that holding company;

“Agency’s Authorised Representative” means the person appointed by the Agency to act on its behalf in carrying out those duties described in this Agreement or any other person nominated by the Agency to act on its behalf and in each case notified in writing to the Client;

“Agreement” means this agreement signed between the Parties;

“Annual Leave”  means unless otherwise stipulated by applicable laws, the Resource shall be

entitled to 22 working days’ leave per year of service to be calculated on a pro-rated basis where

the Resource commence/leave the Engagement part way through the annual leave year; 

“Applicant” means the qualified and experienced Information Technology candidate introduced by the Agency to THE CLIENT for any engagement;

“Base Location” means the location where the Resource is stationed to provide the Services;

“Client’s Authorised Representative” means the person appointed by the Client to act on its behalf  in carrying out those duties described in this Agreement or any other person nominated by the Client to act on its behalf and in each case notified in writing to the Agency;

“Confidential Information” means all information of a commercial proprietary or technical nature disclosed whether in writing verbally or by any other means and whether directly or indirectly by one party to the other whether before or after the date of this Agreement including, but not limited to:

the business, affairs, customers, clients, suppliers, or plans, intentions, or market opportunities of the disclosing party (or of any member of the group of companies to which the disclosing party belongs);

the operations, processes, product information, know-how, designs, trade secrets or software of the disclosing party (or of any member of the group of companies to which the disclosing party belongs); and

this Agreement and any information developed by the parties in the course of carrying out this Agreement.

“Contractual Documentation” means all documentation and other information agreed to be delivered pursuant to this Agreement including software records, reports, documents, papers, relevant computer data and all other technical business and similar information originated by or on behalf of the Agency pursuant to this Agreement;

“Effective Date” means December 01, 2022 

“Engagement” means the Client’s confirmation or acceptance of the Applicant on interim basis to be utilised either onsite or offshore, whether under a contract of service or for services through the Agency to be confirmed through a PO ;

“Fee” means the daily or monthly price to be paid in AED or USD by THE CLIENT to the Agency for the performance of the Services of the selected Resource within the agreed fee structure attached as Appendix 1 (Rate Card) of this Agreement . Proposed fees are to be detailed by the Agencies as per requirement by the Client in a proposal format as and when required by the Client. This shall include, basic salary, allowances for accommodation, utility, transportation, or any other allowances to be mandatorily paid to the Resources by the Agency as per the applicable laws 

“Functional Representative” means the person appointed by the Client and/or Agency to act on its behalf respectively  in carrying out day to day affairs of the engagement such as interview, invoicing, onboarding and other relevant requirements to ensure smooth business process  

“Industry Standards” means the rules and regulations including code of practice in force from time to time relating to the Services to be provided under this Agreement;

“Interim” means period of temporary or termed contract work;

“Introduction” means i) THE CLIENT’s interview of an Applicant in person or by telephone, following THE CLIENT’s instruction to the Agency to search for an Applicant; or ii) the passing to THE CLIENT of a curriculum vitae or information which identifies the Applicant; and in both cases leads to an Engagement of that Applicant if accepted by the Client ;

“Key Performance Indicators (KPI)” means quantifiable measurements, found in Appendix 4, that reflect the critical success factors of the Agency and THE CLIENT; 

“Offshore Resource” means the Resources deployed by the Agency at Agency location or any other location to be agreed between Resource, Agency and the Client  

“Onsite Resource” means the Resources deployed at DP World Office locations globally

"Party" means “the CLIENT” and ‘the Agency” individually 

"Parties" mean THE CLIENT and the Agency collectively;

“Purchase Order or PO” means the work order confirmation to be issued by Client to the Agency electronically on case to case basis confirming the Engagement of any Applicant

"Records" means such accounts and records maintained by the Agency of all costs and fees related to the Engagement under this Agreement and as are reasonably necessary for the purpose of enabling the Client to conduct an audit of that expenditure 

“Resource” means the qualified and experienced Information Technology resource person introduced by the Agency to THE CLIENT for any engagement and selected by the Client.

“Resource Work Product” means the result of any labour, whether physical or mental, by a Resource under an Engagement

“RFP” means Request for Proposal to be issued by CLIENT time to time for the requirement of Professional Resources on interim basis through any manner decided by the CLIENT.

“Services” means the scope of work defined in clause 2 here below  and any agreed variation thereto. It does not refer to the actual work undertaken by the Resource through an Engagement under the supervision of THE CLIENT;

“Sick Leave” means maximum number of 15 working days in a year a Resource is entitled to be absent on medical grounds with submission of required medical reports  

“Working Day” means any day excluding weekly days off and public holidays or as otherwise agreed between the Parties.

2.1 	The Agency will, on the request of the Client:

AAs and when required by the Client, the Agency shall provide THE CLIENT with consistently high-quality Applicants with the correct skills set, experience and aptitude to meet THE CLIENT’s requirements in the most cost effective and professional manner.  

submit the curriculum vitaes to the Client by lodging them in the required form requested by the Client;

assist the Client in scheduling interviews with the Applicant;

undertake reference checks of the Applicant; 

provide various information to the Applicant on behalf of the Client for example, details of benefits, remuneration and other information an Engagement; and

provide all additional assistance to the Client as required in the onboarding of the Applicant for an Engagement.

The Agency shall conduct reference checks and assessments as and when requested by THE CLIENT.

